</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-cae73b4e-42b8-45a5-a763-2d296de6c335"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">The International Day of Education 2025, celebrated annually on 24th January, carries the theme "AI and Education: Preserving Human Agency in a World of Automation." This timely theme sheds light on the evolving relationship between Artificial Intelligence (AI) and education, emphasising the importance of maintaining human rights and autonomy within an increasingly automated world. Hosted by UNESCO, this global event is a platform to discuss innovative solutions, inspire action, and promote quality, equitable education.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-29_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-30_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-31_">The role of AI in education
</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-33_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-a5e7632d-296d-46c3-b5bf-cbac97663727"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">AI has the potential to revolutionise the education sector. From personalised learning experiences to automated administrative tasks, AI is reshaping traditional teaching and learning methods. However, alongside these advancements come critical concerns regarding ethics, equity, and human agency. As we integrate AI into education, it is crucial to ensure that human decision-making and creativity remain at the forefront.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-36_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-37_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-38_">Key benefits of AI in education
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dhFVuh gFqzWs pf-40_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fbKhWw bnrVBh pf-41_"><strong>Personalised learning</strong> - AI-powered tools can tailor learning pathways to individual student needs, promoting inclusivity and better outcomes.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fbKhWw bnrVBh pf-43_"><strong>Administrative efficiency</strong> - Automating routine tasks enables educators to focus more on teaching and student engagement.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fbKhWw bnrVBh pf-45_"><strong>Accessibility </strong>- AI can help bridge educational gaps by providing resources to underserved communities worldwide.
</li></ul><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-47_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-b9d29694-b42e-44c3-a88b-50b0f7f86853"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">While these benefits are promising, the International Day of Education 2025 prompts us to reflect on how we can balance embracing AI and safeguarding fundamental human rights in education.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-50_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-51_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-52_">Preserving human agency in an automated era
</h3><p class="sc-dPZUdm eeluBw pf-54_" data-pf-type="Paragraph4"><input type="checkbox" id="compact-110a1f8a-e6f8-40e0-9012-92bfba51e4ff"/><span class="pf-paragraph-content ">At its core, this year’s theme calls for a harmonious coexistence between AI and human agency. Ensuring that individuals retain control over their learning journeys as automation grows is imperative. This includes protecting privacy, ensuring ethical AI usage, and promoting critical thinking, creativity, and collaboration skills that no machine can replicate.
</span></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-57_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eoVZcn cepmFm pf-58_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-ePDMnc jGJiiy pf-59_">Key questions to address
